cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses computational facial models and their applications in age progression, age estimation, age-invariant facial characterization, and kinship verification. These tasks are all related to computer vision and machine learning, which are the main focus of the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses datasets, evaluation protocols, and metrics, which are also relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses future research directions, which may involve information retrieval techniques, making the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category a possible fit as well.
